**Why FELINE Still Centers on Iron**:

1. Iron is the primary Fenton catalyst in ferroptosis
2. Iron accumulation drives the upstream FELINE cascade
3. Copper amplifies but doesn't initiate the process
4. Zinc toxicity works through iron (via APP-ferroportin disruption)
5. All roads lead back to iron-driven ferroptosis

