- Cairns DM et al. 2022. J Alzheimers Dis. 88(3):1189-1200. [doi:10.3233/JAD-220287](https://doi.org/10.3233/JAD-220287) [PMID: 35754275](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35754275) [Tufts 3D brain model: VZV + quiescent HSV-1 produces tau/A-beta; VZV alone produces no AD pathology]
- Saadatpour F et al. 2025. Brain Res Bull. 230:111506. [doi:10.1016/j.brainresbull.2025.111506](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.brainresbull.2025.111506) [LAT miR-H2/H3 downregulate tau and alpha-syn during latency]
- Zhou Q et al. 2025. Autophagy. 21:2597-2613. [doi:10.1080/15548627.2025.2511584](https://doi.org/10.1080/15548627.2025.2511584) [VZV gM activates CASP3, blocks autophagosome-lysosome fusion via SNAP29 cleavage]
- Rao SS, Adlard PA. 2018. Front Mol Neurosci. 11:276. [doi:10.3389/fnmol.2018.00276](https://doi.org/10.3389/fnmol.2018.00276) [Tau iron-binding motif; mediates iron efflux]
