| Chelation failure                        | Dose/timing issue                      | Removes good iron, leaves bad                                                                                                                                                       |
| Anti-amyloid ARIA                        | Vessel damage                          | Ferroptosis after plaque removal                                                                                                                                                    |
| Progressive MS unresponsive to anti-CD20 | Unclear                                | Iron trapped in microglia, inaccessible to B cell depletion                                                                                                                         |
| Sex differences                          | Unclear                                | Pre-menopausal multi-layer protection → post-menopausal concurrent loss of protections; sex-divergent pathways (men: N→complement; women: multi-layer decline→neuroinflammation) |
| Mixed pathology                          | Coincidence                            | Different responses to same iron challenge                                                                                                                                          |

### 7.3.2 What FELINE Predicts Should Work

1. **Ferroptosis inhibitors** (direct final pathway block)
2. **Lysosomal acidification therapy** (restore L layer)
3. **Combination approaches** (address multiple layers)
4. **Prevention** (viral vaccination, vascular risk, lifestyle)
5. **Stage-specific intervention** (match to layer status)
6. **Iron redistribution** (not chelation; restore flow)

### 7.3.3 What FELINE Predicts Should Fail

1. **Single-target drugs** (only address one layer)
2. **Generic antioxidants** (don't address compartmentalization)
3. **Iron chelation** (removes functional iron)
4. **BACE inhibitors** (block protective A-beta)
5. **TREM2 agonists without lysosomal repair** (can't process what you phagocytose)
6. **Treatment without prevention** (fragments already accumulated)

