## Appendix 7.5: Glossary of Key Terms

| Term                                 | Definition                                                                           |
| ------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **4-HNE**                      | 4-Hydroxynonenal; lipid peroxidation product and marker of ferroptosis               |
| **ALPS index**                 | Along the perivascular space index; DTI-based measure of glymphatic function         |
| **AQP4**                       | Aquaporin-4; water channel polarized to astrocyte endfeet; enables glymphatic flow   |
| **BBB**                        | Blood-brain barrier                                                                  |
| **BSCB**                       | Blood-spinal cord barrier                                                            |
| **BNB**                        | Blood-nerve barrier                                                                  |
| **Ceruloplasmin (Cp)**         | Ferroxidase that oxidizes Fe2+ to Fe3+; required for ferroportin function            |
| **CNI**                        | Calcineurin inhibitor (tacrolimus, cyclosporine)                                     |
| **CypA**                       | Cyclophilin A; activated by APOE4; induces MMP9 and basement membrane degradation    |
| **DAMPs**                      | Damage-associated molecular patterns                                                 |
| **Deferiprone**                | BBB-permeable iron chelator; failed in FAIRPARK-II                                   |
| **DMT1**                       | Divalent metal transporter 1; imports Fe2+ into cells                                |
| **Endfoot**                    | Terminal process of astrocyte that contacts blood vessel                             |
| **Ferritinophagy**             | Autophagic degradation of ferritin to release iron                                   |
| **Ferroptosis**                | Iron-dependent form of regulated cell death involving lipid peroxidation             |
| **Ferroportin (FPN1/SLC40A1)** | Only known cellular iron exporter                                                    |
| **Ferrostatin-1 (Fer-1)**      | Ferroptosis inhibitor                                                                |
| **FELINE**                     | Fe (Iron) - Lysosome - Insulation - Neurovascular - Export; five-layer defense model |
| **GPX4**                       | Glutathione peroxidase 4; master regulator of ferroptosis; reduces lipid peroxides   |
| **GSH**                        | Glutathione; substrate for GPX4                                                      |
| **Hepcidin**                   | Hormone that degrades ferroportin; "iron thermostat"                                 |
| **HERV-K**                     | Human endogenous retrovirus K                                                        |
| **HSV-1**                      | Herpes simplex virus type 1                                                          |
| **LMP**                        | Lysosomal membrane permeabilization                                                  |
| **Liproxstatin-1 (Lip-1)**     | Ferroptosis inhibitor                                                                |
| **mHtt**                       | Mutant huntingtin                                                                    |
| **NAMPT**                      | Nicotinamide phosphoribosyltransferase; rate-limiting NAD+ biosynthesis enzyme       |
| **NAD+**                       | Nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide; required for SIRT3 activity                       |
| **NR**                         | Nicotinamide riboside; NAD+ precursor                                                |
| **NMN**                        | Nicotinamide mononucleotide; NAD+ precursor                                          |
| **NRF2**                       | Nuclear factor erythroid 2-related factor 2; master antioxidant transcription factor |
| **NVU**                        | Neurovascular unit                                                                   |
| **OL**                         | Oligodendrocyte                                                                      |
| **P7C3-A20**                   | NAMPT activator compound                                                             |
| **PANTHOS**                    | Poisonous Anthos; Nixon model of lysosomal AD pathogenesis                           |
| **Pericyte**                   | Mural cell that wraps capillaries; critical for BBB integrity                        |
| **PRL**                        | Paramagnetic rim lesion (in MS)                                                      |
| **PrPC**                       | Cellular (normal) prion protein                                                      |
| **PrPSc**                      | Scrapie (misfolded) prion protein                                                    |
| **PUFA**                       | Polyunsaturated fatty acid; ferroptosis substrate                                    |
| **QSM**                        | Quantitative susceptibility mapping; MRI technique for iron                          |
| **RAB7**                       | Ras-related protein 7; regulates late endosome/lysosome trafficking                  |
| **SASP**                       | Senescence-associated secretory phenotype                                            |
| **SC**                         | Schwann cell                                                                         |
| **SIRT3**                      | Sirtuin 3; mitochondrial deacetylase; regulates GPX4                                 |
| **SLC7A11/xCT**                | Cystine/glutamate antiporter; imports cystine for GSH synthesis                      |
| **sTREM2**                     | Soluble TREM2                                                                        |
| **System xc-**                 | Cystine/glutamate antiporter system                                                  |
| **TDP-43**                     | TAR DNA-binding protein 43                                                           |
| **TFEB**                       | Transcription factor EB; master regulator of lysosomal biogenesis                    |
| **TfR1**                       | Transferrin receptor 1; imports iron into cells                                      |
| **TREM2**                      | Triggering receptor expressed on myeloid cells 2                                     |
| **v-ATPase**                   | Vacuolar ATPase; acidifies lysosomes                                                 |
| **VZV**                        | Varicella-zoster virus                                                               |

